collections.title: Levante UD Tickets & Experiences
collections.descriptionHtml:
Team:

The Levante Union Deportiva, better known as Levante, was founded on September 9, 1909. Players like Juan Puig, Antonio Calpe, Ernesto Domínguez, Sergio Ballesteros, Alberto Rivera, Juanfran García, Iñaki Descarga, Arouna Koné, Félix Ettien, Keylor Navas, Obafemi Martins, José Morales, Felipe Caicedo, Pedja Mijatovic or Johan Cruyff have worn the granota shirt throughout history.

The best time of Levante was, without doubt, the 2011-2012 season when the team finished sixth in La Liga. This allowed him to play the Europa League in 2012-2013 season, a historic achievement for the club. Other key moments in Levante history were the 4 promotions to the first division (1996, 1999, 2004, 2017).

The eternal rival of Levante is Valencia CF. The Valencia derby is surely the best football match we can see in the Ciutat de Valencia stadium, a match full of rivalry and history where tension is assured.

Live the full experience with a host. Get your Levante football tickets and enjoy an unforgettable day in Valencia!

Stadium:

The Ciutat de Valencia Stadium is located in Valencia, Spain. The stadium has a capacity for more than 26.000 spectators.

Get your Ciutat de Valencia tickets and live the best football!
